***Introduction to Dinosaurs


Dinosaurs are a group of reptiles that first appeared during the Triassic period, about 230 million years ago. The word "dinosaur" comes from the Greek words for "terrible lizard". They were the largest land animals of their time, and some were as long as 150 feet from nose to tail. Most dinosaurs were herbivores, but some were carnivores. Scientists believe that dinosaurs became extinct about 65 million years ago, probably because of a meteor or comet that hit the earth, causing the Earth's climate to change so much that the dinosaurs couldn't survive.
